{"ts": "2026-06-09T18:02:45.789945+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The token I have doesn't have write access to this repository, so I cannot add comments or labels. However, here is my complete triage analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Triage Result: **Confirmed Bug**\n\n**Issue #1** — *\"apply_migrations.sh applies files in wrong order on filesystems with case-folding\"*\n\n### Analysis\n\n1. **The problem is real and reproducible by design.** `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` (line 16) uses a bare `for f in migrations/*.sql` loop with **no explicit sort**. The script's own comment acknowledges it *\"relies on shell glob expansion ordering.\"*\n\n2. **Clear dependency chain exists.** The three migration files have a strict ordering requirement:\n   - `001_create_users.sql` → creates `users` table\n   - `002_create_sessions.sql` → creates `sessions` table (references `users`)\n   - `003_add_session_index.sql` → creates index on `sessions(user_id)`\n   \n   If `003` runs before `002`, PostgreSQL correctly errors with `relation \"sessions\" does not exist`.\n\n3. **Root cause is collation-dependent glob ordering.** On case-folding/case-insensitive filesystems (APFS default on macOS, NTFS on Windows), the shell glob expansion order depends on `LC_COLLATE` locale settings and can differ from lexicographic numeric order. This is an environment-specific, non-deterministic behavior.\n\n4. **Fix is straightforward** — sort the glob output explicitly:\n   ```bash\n   for f in $(printf '%s\\n' migrations/*.sql | sort); do\n   ```\n\n### Suggested Labels\n- `bug` — the current code has a real ordering defect on case-folding filesystems.\n- `priority/high` — migration ordering is critical to first-run setup and developer onboarding; a broken migration path blocks all new contributors.\n\n### Limitation\nI was unable to apply labels or post a comment due to token scope restrictions (403 Forbidden). A maintainer with write access should apply the labels and accept the reporter's offer to write the fix.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 521, "prompt_tokens": 13315, "total_tokens": 13836, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 71, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 12800}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "17322ec36bdd45338c6317c235d7c2fb", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead8c-d300-7f00-9512-bb7c1f11f265-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13315, "output_tokens": 521, "total_tokens": 13836, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 12800}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 71}}}}]}}}
